Platinum is historically the correct metal for Art Deco rings — the actual Art Deco period (1920–1940) used platinum exclusively before wartime restrictions forced a shift to white gold. The [Art Deco Fleur-De-Lis](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/art-deco-inspired-fleur-de-lis-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at $1,570 with 101 reviews offers authentic period styling at entry price. See the [oval diamond vintage engagement ring guide](/oval-diamond-vintage-engagement-ring) for the full Art Deco, milgrain, and filigree comparison.

